<HEADLINE> 'Scully' Questions Sex Appeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- At first, Gillian Anderson figured she didn't  
fit the standards for a sex symbol. 
</P>
<P>
	Dana Scully, her character on ``The X-Files,'' is too  
straight-laced, too button-downed. But her popularity kept growing. 
</P>
<P>
	``At first I thought it was bizarre. I just didn't get it,''  
Anderson says in Redbook's February issue. 
</P>
<P>
	``Scully is a change of pace, I guess. There's something about  
her intelligence that mixes with the male fantasy of `What does she 
really look like underneath those tailored suits?''' 
</P>
<P>
	These days, Anderson is a single mom raising a 4-year-old  
daughter. And she is appearing in a new movie, ``Playing by 
Heart,'' with Sean Connery and Jon Stewart. 
</P>
