<HEADLINE> Chargers Fire Trainer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- San Diego Chargers trainer Keoki Kamau was  
fired Saturday after 10 seasons with the team. 
</P>
<P>
	When reached at the team's headquarters, Kamau said he had no  
idea why he was being fired, and said he had no further comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Team spokesman Bill Johnston said the decision was made by  
general manager Bobby Beathard and team president Dean Spanos. 
</P>
<P>
	Beathard didn't shed much light on the situation.  
</P>
<P>
	``The decision was to make a change, and it's something that's  
not easy,'' he said. ``I can't say much more.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Spanos didn't immediately return a telephone call to his home.  
</P>
