<HEADLINE> One of Octuplets Fights Infection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- One of the seven surviving Houston octuplets has  
developed an infection, and one of his sisters was tested Saturday 
for the same problem. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Ikem Louis and his sister Gorom have stopped breast milk  
feedings and are on antibiotic treatment, said Dr. Carol Lynn 
Berseth. Tests on Friday indicated that Ikem had developed an 
infection. His sister Gorom was evaluated Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The two are among eight babies born last month to Nkem Chukwu  
and husband Iyke Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	``The other babies are all progressing on their feedings and  
doing well,'' said Dr. Berseth, the attending neonatologist at 
Texas Children's Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The other five siblings continue to receive breast milk and  
remain in critical but stable condition, Dr. Berseth said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Chukwu, a native of Nigeria, delivered her first baby,  
Ebuka, on Dec. 8. Two weeks later, on Dec. 20, she delivered seven 
more children, led by Chidi. Odera, a girl who weighed 10.3 ounces 
at birth, died a week after birth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
