<HEADLINE> Dixie Dot Com Wins at Santa Anita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Dixie Dot Com scored the biggest victory  
of his career Saturday when he defeated Event of the Year by 4 1/2 
lengths in the $316,000 San Fernando Breeders' Cup Stakes for 
4-year-olds at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by David Flores, Dixie Dot Com covered 1 1-16 miles in  
1:41 and paid $12.40, $4.20 and $3.60. Event of the Year returned 
$3 and $2.60, while Old Topper was another 4 1/2 lengths back in third 
and paid $6.80 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Dixie Dot Com had been second in his last three starts,  
including the Hollywood Derby. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a great way to break our seconditis,'' trainer Bill  
Morey Jr. said. ``We've had some tough seconds, and finally we put 
it together. I think this is his best race. I think our horse 
developed a little more the past year than Event of the Year did.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Event of the Year under Corey Nakatani rallied for second but  
never threatened Dixie Dot Com, who carried six pounds more. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $190,800, increased Dixie Dot Com's career  
earnings to $482,775, with five wins in nine starts. 
</P>
<P>
	In a companion feature, See You Soon overtook Sonja's Faith in  
the closing strides of the $150,000 San Gorgonio Handicap to win by 
a neck. 
</P>
<P>
	See You Soon covered 1 1-8 miles on the turf in 1:49 and paid  
$4.80, $2.80 and $2.60 under Alex Solis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
