<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Padres, Miceli in Three-Year Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Reliever Dan Miceli and the San Diego Padres  
avoided arbitration when they agreed to a $4.6 million, three-year 
contract on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miceli, who was 10-5 with a 3.22 ERA as a setup man for Trevor  
Hoffman, will earn $1.1 million this season, $1.5 million in 2000 
and $2 million in 2001. He made $750,000 last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's developed into one of the better setup guys in  
the league,'' general manager Kevin Towers said. ``He's a guy who 
could close for a lot of other clubs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That leaves left-handed starter Sterling Hitchcock as the only  
Padres player eligible for arbitration. Towers said the two sides 
remain well more than $1 million apart in negotiations for a 
multi-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got our work to do,'' said Towers, who plans to speak at  
length on Sunday with Hitchcock's agent, Tommy Tanzer. Hitchcock 
was MVP of the Padres' NL championship series win over Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
