<HEADLINE> Michigan Gas Blast Kills One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN OAK TOWNSHIP, Mich. (AP) -- Three natural gas explosions  
tore a house apart during the night, killing one woman and injuring 
four other people. 
</P>
<P>
	A gas odor was reported in the area late Friday and a utility  
worker was on the way when the first explosion happened somewhere 
inside the house. 
</P>
<P>
	``The house was just a big ball of flame,'' said neighbor Cassie  
Nance, 26. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire Chief Gary Danforth said he felt the blast at his home four  
or five miles away in the Livingston County community northwest of 
Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
	Consumers Energy Co. crews were working to shut off the house's  
natural gas line four hours later when a second explosion happened 
outside the house, damaging an adjacent convenience store. A third 
blast took place inside the store 40 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the blasts was not immediately determined, Danforth  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	A woman living in the house was killed, authorities said. A male  
occupant of the house, two firefighters and a utility worker were 
treated for burns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
