<HEADLINE> Vikes' Randle Not Expected To Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDEN PRAIRIE, Minn. (AP) -- John Randle's streak of 107  
consecutive starts will likely come to an end on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Randle, the Minnesota Vikings Pro Bowl defensive lineman, said  
his hyperextended left knee was still bothering him and he might 
not start in the NFC Championship Game against Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	``I guess Stalin Colinet will play probably the first quarter,  
the second quarter, and maybe I'll just kind of work myself into 
the game,'' Randle said. ``I may play some nickel situations in the 
first quarter. It just depends on the situation.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Randle, the Vikings sack leader with 10 1/2, hasn't missed a start  
since Nov. 22, 1992. He injured his knee on the final play of 
Minnesota's 41-21 playoff victory over Arizona last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Randle missed practice Wednesday and wore a knee brace during  
practices Thursday and Friday. 
</P>
