<HEADLINE> Americans Sweep Halfpipe Events </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BERCHTESGADEN, Germany (AP) -- Rickey Bower and Kim Stacey gave  
the United States a sweep of the halfpipe events in the World 
Snowboarding Championships on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Bower, 21, from Park City, Utah, won the men's goal medal ahead  
of Fredrik Sterner of Sweden. Timo Aho of Finland was third. 
</P>
<P>
	Stacey, 18, of Stratton Mountain, Vt., clinched the gold ahead  
of Dorian Vidal of France and Anna Hellman of Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
	They were the first gold medals for the Americans in the  
championships, which are held under the auspices of the 
International Skiing Federation. Many leading halfpipe competitors 
who are members of the breakaway International Snowboarding 
Federation stayed away from the championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
